# 💰 Expense Tracker

A modern, responsive personal finance dashboard built with **HTML5, CSS3, and Vanilla JavaScript (ES6)**. Track income and expenses, visualize spending with interactive charts, and manage your financial life — all stored locally in your browser.

![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-active-22C55E) ![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-3B82F6)

---

## ✨ Project Overview

Expense Tracker is a single-page web app that helps you record transactions, categorize spending, and monitor your overall financial health through a clean glassmorphism-style dashboard. All data persists in **Local Storage**, so your transactions are still there when you come back.

---

## 🚀 Features

- **Add / Edit / Delete transactions** with name, amount, category, type, and date
- **Real-time dashboard** — total balance, income, expenses, and savings %, with animated counters
- **Category system** — 11 categories, each with its own icon and color
- **Transaction history** — search, filter (by type/category), and sort (newest, oldest, highest, lowest amount)
- **Analytics charts** (Chart.js) — expense-by-category pie chart, monthly expenses bar chart, income vs. expenses line chart — all auto-updating
- **Quick statistics** — highest expense, most-used category, monthly net summary
- **Monthly budget goal** with a live progress bar
- **CSV export & import** of all transactions
- **Printable PDF report** generation
- **Dark / Light mode** toggle (persisted)
- **Keyboard shortcuts** — `Ctrl/Cmd + K` to focus search, `Esc` to close modals
- **Form validation** with inline error states and toast notifications
- **Delete confirmation modal** to prevent accidental data loss
- **Fully responsive** — desktop, tablet, and mobile layouts via CSS Grid

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

| Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|
| HTML5 | Semantic structure |
| CSS3 | Glassmorphism styling, animations, responsive grid |
| Vanilla JavaScript (ES6) | App logic, state management |
| [Chart.js](https://www.chartjs.org/) | Pie, bar, and line charts |
| Local Storage API | Client-side data persistence |

---

## 📦 Installation

No build tools or dependencies required.

```bash
# Clone or download the project
git clone https://github.com/your-username/expense-tracker.git

# Navigate into the folder
cd expense-tracker

# Open in your browser
open index.html      # macOS
start index.html     # Windows
```

Or simply double-click `index.html`, or serve it with any static server (e.g. `npx serve`).

